SIMPLE: regardant
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Regardant
<hw>Re*gard"ant</hw> <pr>(-<it>a</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>regardant</ets>, fr. <ets>regarder</ets>. See <er>Regard</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>regardant</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Looking behind; looking
backward watchfully.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[He] turns thither his <qex>regardant</qex> eye.</q>
<rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Looking behind or backward;
<as>as, a lion <ex>regardant</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(O.Eng.Law)</fld> <def>Annexed to the land or manor;
<as>as, a villain <ex>regardant</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Regarder</ent>⟦br⟧
